Let's say var upperCaseNames

00:00:53.330 --> 00:00:58.165
and set this to be our animals.forEach.

00:00:58.165 --> 00:01:03.250
Now let's simplify this example by removing the index number.

00:01:03.250 --> 00:01:06.810
Remove the second value from inside here,

00:01:06.810 --> 00:01:09.380
remove the contents from this function.

00:01:09.380 --> 00:01:18.005
Then we can simplify this function by simply returning the animals array.toUpperCase.

00:01:18.005 --> 00:01:23.435
Just like that. Now all we're doing is looping through our original array,

00:01:23.435 --> 00:01:27.499
running a function which will return our animals in upperCase,

00:01:27.499 --> 00:01:30.115
and then store them inside this variable.

00:01:30.115 --> 00:01:36.620
This returns diamond ends the execution of the function and then returns the new value.

00:01:36.620 --> 00:01:38.300
Now we scroll across,

00:01:38.300 --> 00:01:40.265
we can see this upperCaseNames here,

00:01:40.265 --> 00:01:42.080
which has been up on to the screen.

00:01:42.080 --> 00:01:45.050
Now refer to this variable just here.

00:01:45.050 --> 00:01:48.380
If we save this and then reload the browser,

00:01:48.380 --> 00:01:51.710
we get the value of undefined.

00:01:51.710 --> 00:01:56.135
Just hold onto this for now and we'll talk about this more in a moment.

00:01:56.135 --> 00:01:58.940
However, if we change the forEach,

00:01:58.940 --> 00:02:00.810
this time to be map,

00:02:00.810 --> 00:02:03.985
so remove the forEach keyword from here,

00:02:03.985 --> 00:02:06.605
change this to be.map.

00:02:06.605 --> 00:02:08.905
This time if we refresh,

00:02:08.905 --> 00:02:12.965
we now see the values of our array in upperCase.

00:02:12.965 --> 00:02:16.725
This is a key difference between forEach a map,

00:02:16.725 --> 00:02:19.945
only using map will return a new array.

00:02:19.945 --> 00:02:24.730
Basically, forEach will loop all of the items and do something with them,

00:02:24.730 --> 00:02:28.450
such as making them upperCase and pushing them to a new array,

00:02:28.450 --> 00:02:30.250
or even a database.

00:02:30.250 --> 00:02:34.165
Map will also loop over the items and do something with them,

00:02:34.165 --> 00:02:38.800
but it also returns a new array with the transformed items,

00:02:38.800 --> 00:02:43.060
which will have access to by storing them inside of this variable.

00:02:43.060 --> 00:02:44.995
